# Documented Trivy exceptions for backend/Dockerfile (tally-api).
#
# All entries below are Debian OS packages pulled in transitively by
# python:3.12-slim-bookworm that our FastAPI app never invokes. Each is either
# marked will_not_fix or fix_deferred upstream (Debian has no patch to apply),
# and the vulnerable code path is not reachable from this application. See
# docs/adr/0003-trivy-exceptions.md for the fuller rationale and the plan to
# revisit this (e.g. a distroless base image) once it can be verified against
# a real Docker build.

# zlib: integer overflow in zipOpenNewFileInZip4_6 (minizip). Debian: will_not_fix.
# We never call minizip; zlib is only used transitively via Python's stdlib zlib module.
CVE-2023-45853

# perl-base / perl-Archive-Tar / perl-IO-Compress: path traversal, DoS, arbitrary
# file access via crafted tar archives. Debian: fix_deferred. perl-base ships as
# part of Debian's essential package set but is never invoked by this application
# (no perl scripts, no tar extraction via perl).
CVE-2026-42496
CVE-2026-42497
CVE-2026-48962
CVE-2026-9538
CVE-2026-8376

# gzip: buffer overflow in the LZH decompression path. The gzip binary is never
# invoked by this application (Caddy/uvicorn handle any compression needed).
CVE-2026-41992

# libacl1: symlink traversal privilege escalation via libacl functions. Not
# called by this application.
CVE-2026-54369

# ncurses (libncursesw6, libtinfo6, ncurses-base, ncurses-bin): buffer overflow.
# No interactive terminal use inside the container.
CVE-2025-69720

# libsqlite3-0: integer overflow. Python's sqlite3 stdlib module is never used
# by this application — all persistence goes through Postgres/SQLAlchemy.
CVE-2025-7458
